The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for generative modeling, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on denoising auto-encoders and their use as generative models. This makes the most likely sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these models for image data, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely option. The paper also discusses the use of these models for inference and optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options. Finally, the paper mentions the use of these models for natural language processing, which suggests the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a less likely but still possible option.
